1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Nc3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 O-O 8. Bd3 c5 9. O-O Nc6 10. d5 Bxc3!? 11. Bh6 Nd4!? { Sacking the exchange, but keeping the important dark squared bishop on an extremely strong post. } 12. Nxd4 Bxd4 13. Bxf8 Qxf8 14. Rc1 e5? 15. Qa4 Qh6 (15... Qd8 { A better move that accomplishes the same idea without allowing any Qe8+ ideas from white }) 16. Bc4 Qg5 17. Qe8+ Kg7 18. d6 Bh3 19. Qxf7+ Kh6 20. Qf3 Bg4 21. Qa3 Rf8 22. Kh1!! { The only saving move in the position. Otherwise Bf3! wins the queen. } 22... Bxf2?? { Completely missing Rc2 in response... } (22... Rxf2 23. Rxf2 Bxf2 24. Rf1 Bd4) 23. Rc2 Qh4 24. Rcxf2 Rxf2 25. Qe3+ Rf4 26. g3 Qh3 { The last try. gxf4 was almost played by white - blundering the queen. } 27. Rxf4 exf4 28. Qxf4+ Kh5 29. Bf1 { Trapping the queen and finishing the attack with finesse. } *


