1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7 7. Qg4 O-O 8. Bd3 Nbc6 9. Qh5 Ng6 10. Nf3 c4?? { [%cal Gf3g5] } (10... Qc7 11. Be3 c4 12. Bxg6 fxg6 13. Qg4 { My actual theory. }) 11. Be2? (11. Bxg6 fxg6 12. Qg4 { The line I expected from white (misremembering from another line in the Winowar) }) (11. Ng5! h6 12. Nxf7 Rxf7 13. Bxg6 Rf8 { The only way to take advantage of the blunder I played }) 11... Qa5 { Infiltrating the queenside before white has castled. } 12. Bd2 Qa4 { Further infiltration } 13. Bd1? (13. Ra2 { Active defense is always better than passive defense. }) 13... Bd7 14. Ng5 h6 15. Nh3 Nce7 16. Bxh6? { I expected this sacrifice. But with two knights around my king, I should be fine. } 16... gxh6 17. Qxh6 Nf5 18. Qg5 Qa5 { I saw this far before the sacrifice and thought I would be OK. } 19. Qd2 Kg7 20. g4 Nh6 21. f4 Qd8 22. g5?? { Giving away the f5 outpost for nothing in return. } 22... Nf5 23. Bh5 (23. Bg4 Rh8 24. Bxf5 exf5 { I figured this would be a better try, but my light-squared bishop is still around to defend these terrible pawns. }) 23... Rh8 24. Bxg6 Kxg6 25. Nf2 Rh4! { Stopping Ng4 getting into f6 - my only weak square. } 26. O-O? Qh8 27. h3 Ba4 { While not strictly necessary, I wanted to get my bishop outside the pawn chain before I went in for the kill on the kingside. } 28. Rab1 b5 29. Kh2 Qh7 30. Rg1 Rh8 31. Rg3 { There's no defense anyway. } (31. Kg2 Rxh3 32. Nxh3 Qxh3+ 33. Kf2 Bxc2 34. Qxc2 Qe3+ 35. Kf1 Rh3 36. Rb2 Rf3+ 37. Kg2 Rg3+ 38. Kf1 Rxg1#) 31... Nxg3 32. Kxg3 Rxh3+ 33. Nxh3 Qxh3+ 34. Kf2 Qh2+ 35. Ke3 (35. Ke1 Qg1+ 36. Ke2 Qg2+ 37. Kd1 Rh1+ 38. Qe1 Qxc2#) 35... Rh3# *


