1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e6 6. Be3 d5 7. Nxc6?! (7. exd5 exd5) 7... bxc6 8. e5 Nd7 9. f4 Bb4 10. Qd2 c5 { [%cal Gd5d4] } 11. a3 Bxc3 12. bxc3 O-O 13. Bd3 c4 14. Be2 a5 15. O-O Rb8 16. Rab1 Ba6 17. Kh1 Qe7 18. a4 Nc5 { The knight would be too strong on e4, so it is taken out by my bad bishop. } { [%cal Gc5e4] } 19. Bxc5 Qxc5 20. Qd4 Qa3?? 21. f5 { Figuring I was down on position because my weak pawns are about to drop, I committed to an attack with f5. I didn't stop to think about loose pieces! } 21... Rxb1 22. Rxb1 Qxa4 23. f6 Qxc2! { Defends on g6 with tempo against both pieces. } 24. Re1 g5?! 25. Bh5 Qd3 26. Qg4 (26. Qb6! Bc8 27. Qc7 Qf5 28. Bxf7+! Rxf7 29. Qxc8+ Rf8 { And white is better due to the passed f pawn. }) 26... Qd2 (26... h6) 27. Rf1 h6 28. h4 Qd3?? { Trying to defend the weakened light squares and trade queens with Qe4. } (28... Qxc3 29. hxg5) 29. Rf3?? (29. Rf4!! { Saves the rook and stops any ideas of queen trading. White breaks through on g5. } 29... Kh7 (29... Qxc3 30. hxg5 Qc1+ 31. Kh2 c3 32. gxh6+ Kh7 33. Qg7#) 30. hxg5 hxg5 31. Qxg5) 29... Qe4 { [%cal Gh4g5,Ge4g4,Gh5g4,Gh6g5] } 30. Qxe4 dxe4 31. Re3 Bb7 32. hxg5 hxg5 33. Be2 Kh7 34. Rg3 Kg6 35. Bg4!? { Stopping further penetration of the king and setting up some king nets. } 35... Rd8 36. Rh3 Rd3 37. Rh8! Rxc3? { With the king trapped, a draw should be the result of this game. } (37... Rd7 38. Rg8+ Kh7 39. Rg7+ Kh6 { Rd7 was the only move to defend f7 and therefore push the a pawn to victory lane. }) 38. Rg8+ Kh6 39. Rh8+ Kg6 40. Rg8+ Kh7 { Black wanted more than a draw here, so allowed white to take on f7. } (40... Kh6) 41. Rg7+ Kh6 42. Rxf7 Rc1+ 43. Kh2 Bd5 44. Ra7?? { Getting behind the passed a pawn, but missing that the bishop covered the retreat square on a8. } 44... Rf1 45. Rxa5 Rf2?? { With the idea of e3! Attacking g2 and defending the rook. But it's not working... } 46. Rxd5!! exd5 47. e6! Kg6 (47... Rxf6 48. e7 { The other line also does not stop the promotion. The bishop covers e6 and the pawn covers f8. }) 48. e7 Kf7 49. Bh5+ Kxf6 50. e8=Q Rf4 51. Bf7 Kg7 52. Bxd5 c3 53. Qe5+ Kh6 54. Bxe4 Rh4+ 55. Kg3 Rf4 56. Qh8# *


