1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 d5 3. e3 c5 4. c3 Qb6 5. Qb3 c4 6. Qxb6 axb6 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Be2 b5 9. O-O b4 10. Nbd2 Bf5 11. Ne5 e6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. cxb4 Bxb4 14. Nf3 O-O 15. Ne5 Rfc8 16. a3 Be7 17. Rfc1 c5 18. a4 cxd4 19. exd4 Bb4 20. Bg5 Ne4 21. Be3 f6 22. Nd7 Rc7 23. Nc5 Nxc5 24. dxc5 Bxc5 25. Bxc5 Rxc5 26. b3 cxb3 27. Rxc5 b2 28. Rd1 b1=Q 29. Rxb1 Bxb1 30. a5 d4 31. Rb5 Be4 32. Bc4 Kf7 33. f3 Bc6 34. Rc5 Bd7 35. Kf2 Ke7 36. a6 Kd6 37. Ra5 e5 38. Ke2 Ra7 39. Kd3 Bc6 40. Bg8 h6 41. Bh7 (41. Kc4 g5) 41... g5 42. Bf5 h5 (42... Kc7! { Transfer the king towards the weak pawn before white has a chance to infiltrate with Kc4-c5. } 43. Kc4 Kb6 44. Ra1 Rxa6 45. Rxa6+ Kxa6 46. Kc5 Bb5 47. Kd6 d3) 43. Kc4 h4 44. Bc8 Kc7 45. Rc5 Kd6 46. Ra5 Kc7 47. Rc5 Kd6 (47... Kxc8 48. Rxc6+ Rc7! { Blocking the check and pinning the white rook! This was the move I missed that would have won the game. }) 48. Ra5 { Draw was agreed. } *


