1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. Bf4 d5 4. c4?! { I don't know any theory on the Trompowsky, so didn't recognize that c4 is a mistake. } 4... e6 (4... e5!! 5. dxe5 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Bc5 7. e3 d4 8. Qf3 dxe3 9. Qxe4 (9. Bxe3 Bb4+ 10. Nc3 Nxc3 11. a3) 9... exf2+ 10. Kd1 fxg1=Q 11. Rxg1 Bxg1) 5. Nc3 g5 6. Bc1 Bb4 7. Qb3 a5?! { Attack the weakened center instead! } (7... c5! 8. cxd5 O-O 9. dxe6 Bxe6 $16) 8. Nf3 Nc6 9. e3 a4 10. Qc2 g4 (10... a3!! { A truly destabilizing move that I completely missed. }) 11. Nd2 Nxc3 12. bxc3 Be7 13. Bd3 h5 14. O-O { My king does not belong on the kingside, queenside, or in the center. Out of improving moves, I decide to shuffle my king. } 14... Kf8 15. e4!? { Trying to nuke the center while the black king stays there. } 15... Bg5 16. f3 Be3+ 17. Kh1 g3! { Complicating matters and potentially opening up the white king as well. } 18. e5 h4 (18... Qh4 19. h3 Bf4 { I didn't see how this would be good for black, but it ends much better than in the game. }) 19. h3 Ne7 20. f4 dxc4 { Finally black gives up the center just to get a square on d5 and the diagonal towards white's king. It's too little too late. } 21. Nxc4 Bxc1 22. Raxc1 Nd5 23. Qd2 { The threat of f5 is too strong, but black should have just stuck to his guns instead of retreating. } 23... Ne7 24. Ne3 b6 25. f5 exf5 26. Nxf5 Nxf5 27. Bxf5 Bxf5 28. Rxf5 { I was happy to trade off all my bad pieces for white's active ones. But black is not out of the woods at all. } 28... Ra5?! { A psuedo-active move. The rook doesn't do anything from a5. } 29. Rcf1 Rh7 30. Rxf7+?? { Looks like it should be winning, but the best white can hope for is a draw here. } 30... Rxf7 31. Qh6+ Kg8 32. Qg6+ Rg7 33. Qe6+ Kh8 34. Qh6+ Kg8 35. Qe6+ Kh8 36. Rf6?? { White wants more, but in fact there isn't anything after Ra8 } 36... Rd5 (36... Ra8 37. Rh6+ Rh7 38. Qg6 Qe7 $19) 37. Qf5 Kg8 38. Qe6+ Kh8 39. Qf5 { Black missed the win at the end, but was happy for a draw given how bad things were at move 29. } *


